text of land cover change impact on climate. The experiments herein illustrate that deforestation triggers two opposite types of forcing mechanisms‚Äîradiative forcing (owing to surface albedo change) and nonradiative forcing (owing to change in evapotranspiration efficiency and surface roughness)‚Äîthat exhibit a similar magnitude globally. However, when applying the radiative forcing concept, nonradiative processes are ignored, which may lead to a misrepresentation of land cover change impact on climate.},
